President Obama met with American Muslim leaders to discuss various domestic and foreign policy issues. They discussed topics such as the Affordable Care Act, anti-Muslim violence and discrimination, the 21st Century Policing Task Force, and the upcoming White House Summit on Countering Violence Extremism. The President expressed his commitment to safeguarding civil rights and discussed the need to counter groups like ISIL that commit acts of violence in the name of Islam. He encouraged the Muslim leaders to remain engaged in their communities and expressed his interest in continuing the discussion on these and other issues.